  "body": "**Motivation**\r\n\r\nI am currently trying to compile my project, which uses OZ contracts v3.4-solc-0.7, with [solang](https://github.com/hyperledger-labs/solang)\r\n\r\n**Problems**\r\n\r\n1) `solang` can not handle the assembly code, like in `utils/Address.sol` or `contracts/cryptography/ECDSA.sol`\r\n \r\n```\r\n/project/node_modules/@openzeppelin/contracts/cryptography/ECDSA.sol:40:9-44:10: error: evm assembly not supported on target solana\r\nLine 40:\r\n\tassembly {            r := mload(add(signature, 0x20))            s := mload(add(signature, 0x40))            v := byte(0, mload(add(signature, 0x60)))        }\r\n\t^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould a contract version not making use of assembly be possible ?\r\n\r\n\r\n2) `solang` has also issues with `AccessControl.sol` which import `utils/Address.sol` , but does it actually need `utils/Address.sol` ??\r\n\r\n",
